                                   A BILL

To reorient national defense posture from power-projection toward resilience-
based security consistent with the commons infrastructure established by the
Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act; to govern automated
systems deployed in commons-critical infrastructure; to establish an open-source
analytics commons and mandate the commons contribution of intelligence-community-
funded analytics platforms; to prohibit algorithmic governance of individual
rights; to provide for the protection of the Federated Network against foreign
and domestic sabotage; to establish an automation dividend ensuring that
productivity gains from automated production are distributed through the commons
rather than concentrated in private hands; and to provide for the long-term
strategic security of the United States on foundations of material resilience
rather than petrodollar protection.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States
of America in Congress assembled,

