In this Act:

(1) ANALYTICS COMMONS.-- The term "Analytics Commons" means the federated,
open-source data integration and decision-support infrastructure established
under Title III of this Act, comprising commons-governed software tools,
governance datasets, and coordination platforms that provide Qualified Federated
Networks with the analytical capabilities necessary to govern their resource
flows, monitor commons health, and coordinate inter-network exchanges, and that
are held as commons resources under the Intellectual Property Commons established
by the Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(2) AUTOMATION DIVIDEND.-- The term "Automation Dividend" means the mechanism
established under Section 402 of Title IV of this Act by which productivity gains
generated by automated systems deployed within the Federated Network are
distributed to Commons Members through reductions in required labor contributions,
improvements to the Guaranteed Provision Standard, and contributions to the
Bootstrap Grant Program, rather than through accumulation by any individual
member, enterprise, or external party.

(3) COMMONS AUTOMATION PRINCIPLE.-- The term "Commons Automation Principle"
means the governing principle established under Section 401 of Title IV of this
Act that automated systems deployed within the Federated Network are governed as
commons resources whose productive output serves the material wellbeing of all
Commons Members, that no automated system deployed in commons infrastructure
may be used to concentrate productive gains in any individual or enterprise at
the expense of the broader membership, and that automation serves the commons
rather than replacing it.

(4) COMMONS MEMBER.-- The term "Commons Member" has the meaning given such term
in Section 4(4) of the Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(5) FEDERATED COMMONS MEMBERSHIP.-- The term "Federated Commons Membership"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(7) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(6) FEDERATED MESH OPEN STANDARD or FMOS.-- The term "Federated Mesh Open
Standard" has the meaning given such term in Section 4(9) of the Federal
Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(7) GUARANTEED PROVISION STANDARD.-- The term "Guaranteed Provision Standard"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(10) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(8) HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP LAYER or HITL.-- The term "Human-in-the-Loop Layer" has
